30/09/2010
BERLIN, Germany -- Authorities say a Croatian citizen attacked Croatia's consulate general in the German city of Dusseldorf on Wednesday (September 29th).
The man, 56, allegedly threw two petrol bombs at the building and caused minor damage but no injuries.
Police say his motives were personal and there is no evidence suggesting he belongs to any group.
(HRT, HINA, radio Free Europe - 29/09/10)
